  "key_transit_note": "0.02° · exact June 11",
  "prose": [
    "What the North Node does at natal Jupiter in the 5th is not expand the work. Jupiter already handles expansion. It asks whether the work is the path. At 0.02° from exact, tightest today before contact tomorrow, the answer has nearly arrived. Natal Jupiter in Scorpio 5th is the place where creative engagement goes all the way in or not at all. The Node circling back retrograde to find this point, Pisces to Scorpio, water sign to water sign, has the quality of a circuit completing rather than a door opening. The path was always pointed here. The trine just confirms it.",
    "Jupiter's trine to natal Pluto peaked yesterday at 0.02° and has opened to 0.22° separating. That window closed. The structural confirmation—that the depth and scale of what's being built belong where they are—passed through. The Venus-Jupiter Cancer conjunction is still at 0.53°, the water-trine current still flowing into the Scorpio 5th, though its sharpest moment is behind you. What continues is the current; what's finished is the peak pressure.",
    "Mercury squares Saturn in the sky today at 0.17°, exact this afternoon—Cancer mind meeting Aries structure (transit-to-transit). The instinct under this square is to elaborate, to soften, to wrap the point in context before stating it. The better move is the reverse. Say the direct version of the thing you've been approaching with preamble. The structure will hold it.",
    "Uranus continues closing toward natal Jupiter (5th): 0.27° applying, exact June 14, four days out. The same natal point the Node is reaching in recognition, Uranus is redirecting in form. They don't cancel. The Node says the path runs through here; Uranus says something in how the work is structured needs to shift before it can expand in the direction the path is pointing. Both are right."
  ],
  "pull": "Write the thing you've been approaching sideways.",
